DECI.ARATION OF. IARED ISAACMAN

I, Jared Isaacman, declare as follows:

1.  l am over the age of eighteen and am competent to make this Declaration. I
    have personal knowledge of the facts set forth in this Declaration and, if called upon to do so,
    could and would testify competently thereto.

2.  I am the Chief Executive Officer of Shift4 Payments, LLC (“Shift4”).  I have
    held this position since Shift4's acquisition of Shift4 Corporation in late 2017. From 2003 to
    2017, I served as the Chief Executive Officer of Shift4 Corporation.  I have also held a position
    on Shift4's board of directors since2017 .

3.  I participated in the negotiation of the 2018 Reseller Agreement between
    Card Connect and Shift4 on behalf of Shift4.

4.   The parties to the Reseller Agreement never discussed prohibiting Shift4 from

supporting Payfacs that use First Data as their payment processor.

5.  I have reviewed the information in Card Connect’s Response to Shift4’s Local

Rule 56.1 Statement of Uncontested Material Facts at paragraph 49, which includes the following

statement, “Shift4’s core product is the gateway services.”

6.	As of March 2018, Shift4’s core product was payment processing services.

7.  As of the date of the Reseller Agreement, Marketplace was in a conceptual

stage.

8.  I understand that Card Connect has produced a document with Bates number

CC-00004958, that has been designated Confidential. I have reviewed the document and it

does not alter or change any of my responses.

9.  I have reviewed Card Connect’s representation, in its Supplemental Response to
Interrogatory Number 9, of a May 7,2018 text message I sent to Randy Miskanic. While the

represcntation of the text message is acctrate, it is incomplete and out of context.
